WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:03.834
PREVIOUSLY ON
DAWSON'S CREEK...

00:03.834 --> 00:04.834
JOEY, WE WON...

00:04.834 --> 00:05.834
THE BOSTON
FILM FESTIVAL.

00:05.834 --> 00:08.291
I WAS HOPING THAT YOU
WOULD PRODUCE AGAIN.

00:08.291 --> 00:09.917
I DON'T THINK I CAN.
I...

00:09.917 --> 00:12.708
MAYBE IT'S TIME FOR
A LITTLE IMPULSIVE BEHAVIOR

00:12.708 --> 00:13.667
FOR A CHANGE, DAWSON.

00:13.667 --> 00:16.000
[LAUGHS]

00:16.000 --> 00:18.291
ONE MINUTE YOU'RE
LAUGHING, AND THE NEXT
YOU'RE IN TEARS.

00:18.291 --> 00:20.000
I'M FINE, JACK.

00:20.000 --> 00:22.291
MAYBE IT'S TIME YOU WENT
BACK ON YOUR MEDICATION.

00:22.291 --> 00:25.417
MY MOTHER AND MY SISTER,
THEY DEPEND ON ME
TO BE THE ROCK. ME.

00:25.417 --> 00:26.333
I UNDERSTAND IT.

00:26.333 --> 00:28.041
I JUST WISH YOU'D
LET ME HELP YOU.

00:32.667 --> 00:34.500
I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE SAYING THIS.

00:34.500 --> 00:38.834
I MEAN, AFTER ALL THESE YEARS
OF HIDING BEHIND HIGHBROW
ANALYTICAL POSTURING--

00:38.834 --> 00:41.500
I'M SAYING IT.

00:41.500 --> 00:42.917
I LOVE YOU.

00:42.917 --> 00:45.291
I--I KNOW
IT'S NONSENSICAL.

00:45.291 --> 00:46.875
"NONSENSICAL"? IT'S INSANE.

00:46.875 --> 00:48.667
WE'VE KNOWN EACH OTHER
FOR 15 YEARS.

00:48.667 --> 00:51.625
YOU COULDN'T FIND SOME OTHER
TIME TO FREUDIAN SLIP THIS CAT
OUT OF THE BAG?

00:51.625 --> 00:54.375
I'VE WANTED TO...
SO MANY TIMES.

00:54.375 --> 00:57.000
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW LONG I'VE BEEN
WRESTLING INTERNALLY

00:57.000 --> 00:59.625
WITH THE PSYCHOLOGICAL
REPERCUSSIONS
OF MY FEELINGS.

00:59.625 --> 01:01.041
I NEED SOME TIME TO PROCESS.

01:01.041 --> 01:05.000
I MEAN, MY ELECTRICAL SYNAPSES
ARE ON OVERLOAD HERE.

01:05.000 --> 01:07.875
MY BRAIN IS TELLING ME
ONE THING, BUT MY HEART,

01:07.875 --> 01:09.166
IT SAYS ANOTHER.

01:09.166 --> 01:12.834
IT'S TELLING ME THAT I SHOULD
CONSIDER THE UNEQUIVOCAL,

01:12.834 --> 01:16.542
HIGHLY IRRATIONAL,
POSSIBLY DAMAGING
PROPOSITION OF...

01:16.542 --> 01:18.542
OF LOVING YOU BACK.

01:18.542 --> 01:23.166
WAIT...

01:27.041 --> 01:28.291
YOU MISSED A LINE.

01:28.291 --> 01:30.250
YOU FORGOT
HYPNOTICALLY SCARRING...

01:30.250 --> 01:32.125
SO IF YOU WANT IT DONE
RIGHT, YOU GET AN ACTOR.

01:32.125 --> 01:34.041
I'M NOT EXACTLY COMFORTABLE
PLAYING THE GIRL HERE.

01:34.041 --> 01:35.458
SO WHAT DO YOU THINK?

01:35.458 --> 01:38.083
I MEAN, DO YOU
THINK IT WOULD MAKE
A GOOD MOVIE?

01:38.083 --> 01:40.542
YOU WRITE
IN TOO MANY SYLLABLES.

01:40.542 --> 01:42.417
AND WHAT'S WITH ALL THIS
PSYCHOBABBLE INSIGHT?

01:42.417 --> 01:43.750
HOW MANY TEENAGERS
DO YOU KNOW
THAT TALK LIKE THAT?

01:43.750 --> 01:47.542
SYLLABLES ASIDE,
DO YOU THINK IT WILL
MAKE A GOOD MOVIE?

01:47.542 --> 01:51.083
YEAH, YEAH. HOWEVER,
YOU DID MAKE JOEY A LITTLE
BIT ON THE ANGRY SIDE,

01:51.083 --> 01:52.291
EVEN FOR HER.

01:52.291 --> 01:53.250
[LAUGHS]

01:53.250 --> 01:54.875
THAT'S NOT JOEY.

01:54.875 --> 01:57.375
RIGHT. THAT'S NOT JOEY,
THE GUY'S NOT YOU,

01:57.375 --> 01:59.750
AND YOU'RE NOT DISSECTING
YOU TWO'S RELATIONSHIP
ON THE PAGE

01:59.750 --> 02:02.417
JUST LIKE EVERY OTHER
NARCISSISTIC WRITER
THROUGH HISTORY.

02:02.417 --> 02:05.250
JUST TELL ME
WHAT YOU THINK.

02:05.250 --> 02:06.917
WELL, I THINK IT'S DARK.

02:06.917 --> 02:08.125
IT'S OBTUSE.

02:08.125 --> 02:09.875
IT'S VERY UN-DAWSON LEERY.

02:10.875 --> 02:12.291
THANK YOU.

02:12.291 --> 02:16.417
I...THIS IS THE FIRST TIME
I'VE BEEN ABLE TO WRITE
SOMETHING

02:16.417 --> 02:17.750
THAT'S NOT
JUST PLOT DRIVEN,

02:17.750 --> 02:19.458
BUT ALSO
EMOTIONALLY DRIVEN.

02:19.458 --> 02:23.208
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU'RE EVOLVING AS
AN ARTIST.

02:23.208 --> 02:25.542
IT'S ABOUT TIME I TOOK
SOME RISKS, YOU KNOW.

02:25.542 --> 02:26.792
RIDE THE EDGE A LITTLE.

02:26.792 --> 02:30.375
WELL,
IF THAT'S THE CASE,
I DO HAVE ONE NOTE.

02:30.375 --> 02:32.500
WHICH IS?

02:32.500 --> 02:34.625
WHY DON'T THEY HAVE SEX?

02:34.625 --> 02:36.625
I MEAN, I KNOW YOU AND
JOEY NEVER DID
IN REAL LIFE,

02:36.625 --> 02:37.583
BUT THIS IS A FILM.

02:37.583 --> 02:38.458
YOU CAN WRITE IT ANY WAY
YOU WANT.

02:38.458 --> 02:40.792
YOU KNOW,
TAKE THE RISKY PLUNGE.

02:40.792 --> 02:42.375
AH, SEE, I HAVE.

02:42.375 --> 02:44.750
HOW MANY MOVIES DO YOU
SEE WHERE A BUNCH
OF HORNY TEENAGERS

02:44.750 --> 02:47.333
JUST GO AT IT
LIKE RABBITS? HUH?

02:47.333 --> 02:48.583
I MEAN, THAT'S
THE SAFE CHOICE.

02:48.583 --> 02:52.959
THE RISKY, EDGIER CHOICE
IS TO HAVE THEM NOT DO IT.

02:52.959 --> 02:56.959
ONLY YOU TAKE YOUR
VIRGINAL INSECURITIES
AND FEAR OF DEFLOWERMENT

02:56.959 --> 02:58.500
AND TURN THEM INTO
RISKY, EDGY BEHAVIOR.

02:58.500 --> 03:01.333
OH, YEAH, I HAVE NO
PROBLEM BEING A VIRGIN.

03:01.333 --> 03:04.959
I'M SORRY IF MY...CONFIDENCE
AND MY CONVICTIONS
DISCOMBOBULATE YOU.

03:04.959 --> 03:08.291
"DISCOMBOBULATE"?

03:08.291 --> 03:09.834
HOW MANY SYLLABLES
IS THAT?

03:59.959 --> 04:03.333
[♪♪♪]

04:13.625 --> 04:16.625
Jen: HEY, WE'RE
HOLDING AUDITIONS
FOR A MOVIE TODAY

04:16.625 --> 04:17.666
HOPE YOU CAN MAKE IT.

04:17.666 --> 04:18.834
HEY.
HEY, YOU.

04:18.834 --> 04:20.750
SO HOW'S INTEREST?
ARE WE GONNA HAVE
A TURNOUT?

04:20.750 --> 04:22.166
AS A FIRST-TIME PRODUCER,

04:22.166 --> 04:25.083
MY INSTINCTS TELL ME WE'RE
GONNA HAVE A HUGE TURNOUT,
DAWSON.

04:25.083 --> 04:26.291
COOL.

04:26.291 --> 04:26.959
WE'RE HOLDING AUDITIONS
FOR A MOVIE TODAY.

04:26.959 --> 04:29.208
COME ON BY, ALL RIGHT?

04:29.208 --> 04:30.750
YOU'RE SUCH A NATURAL.
YOU'RE SO GOOD AT THIS.

04:30.750 --> 04:32.000
OH, THANKS.

04:32.000 --> 04:34.583
DON'T EXPECT TOO MUCH.
I MEAN, I'M NO JOEY.
PLEASE.

04:34.583 --> 04:37.375
SHE DIDN'T HAVE
ANY EXPERIENCE EITHER
WHEN SHE FIRST STARTED.

04:37.375 --> 04:38.333
YOU'RE GONNA BE GOOD.

04:38.333 --> 04:40.667
I HAVE THE UTMOST
CONFIDENCE IN YOU.

04:40.667 --> 04:44.667
WHY, THANK YOU.
MR. WRITER SLASH DIRECTOR.

04:44.667 --> 04:45.792
[LAUGHS]

04:45.792 --> 04:47.834
HEY, BE SURE YOU GET
A FLIER TO JAMES LOWELL.

04:47.834 --> 04:49.000
HE'D BE PERFECT FOR
THE LEAD.

04:49.000 --> 04:52.125
EW!
EW?

04:52.125 --> 04:54.583
JEN, HE'S LIKE
THE CLASSIC LEADING GUY.

04:54.583 --> 04:56.917
HE'S KIND, HE'S FUNNY,
HE'S SELF-EFFACING.

04:56.917 --> 04:58.458
