14:01.792 --> 14:02.834
WHAT YOU GOT IN THE BAG?

14:02.834 --> 14:03.875
UH, NOTHING.

14:03.875 --> 14:06.458
HEY, UH...
PACEY, PLEASE.

14:06.458 --> 14:08.000
JUST GIVE IT BACK!

14:08.000 --> 14:11.166
UH, "ANDREA McPHEE.
TAKE 2 TABLETS DAILY
AS DIRECTED.

14:11.166 --> 14:13.000
ZANAX."

14:13.000 --> 14:15.375
ZANAX. THAT'S, UH...

14:15.375 --> 14:17.834
THAT'S FOR SEVERE
DEPRESSION AND ANXIETY,
RIGHT?

14:17.834 --> 14:19.834
IT'S LIKE PROZAC, SO...

14:19.834 --> 14:23.458
UH, IT'S MY MOM'S.
WE HAVE THE SAME
FIRST NAME--ANDREA.

14:23.458 --> 14:26.125
UM...PLEASE, PACEY,
YOU KNOW I'M SENSITIVE
ABOUT HER.

14:26.125 --> 14:27.375
YEAH, YEAH,
I'M REALLY SORRY.

14:27.375 --> 14:28.708
I DIDN'T KNOW. OH, GOD.

14:28.708 --> 14:30.500
IT'S OK.

14:30.500 --> 14:31.375
YOU'RE SUCH
A GOOD DAUGHTER.

14:31.375 --> 14:34.125
[LAUGHS]

14:34.125 --> 14:34.458
SO WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

14:34.458 --> 14:36.208
OH--

14:36.208 --> 14:37.500
[CLEARS THROAT]
NOTHING.

14:37.500 --> 14:39.542
I WAS JUST PICKING UP
SOME STUFF.

14:39.542 --> 14:44.208
IN THE, UH,
CONDOM SECTION?

14:44.208 --> 14:46.458
[STUMBLING]

14:46.458 --> 14:47.959
I HAD NO IDEA.

14:47.959 --> 14:49.625
IT'S VERY ODD,
DON'T YOU THINK?

14:49.625 --> 14:52.458
YOU DON'T THINK THIS
IS A SIGN, LIKE THE LOVE
GODS ARE TRYIN' TO...

14:52.458 --> 14:54.375
HELP US OUT OR--

14:54.375 --> 14:56.542
NO, I THINK
THAT WOULD BE YOU.

14:56.542 --> 14:58.458
I'M JUST ENGAGING
IN A LITTLE INNUENDO

14:58.458 --> 14:59.458
IN THE HOPES
THAT MAYBE SOMEDAY

14:59.458 --> 15:01.542
IT'LL LEAD TO SOMETHING
A LITTLE MORE...

15:01.542 --> 15:02.625
TANGIBLE.

15:02.625 --> 15:06.875
HEY, I MEAN, I'M ALL
FOR DISCOVERING THE, UH,

15:06.875 --> 15:09.875
PHYSICAL SIDE
OF PACEY WITTER.

15:09.875 --> 15:12.041
I JUST DON'T KNOW THAT
I'M ENTIRELY PREPARED YET.

15:12.041 --> 15:13.750
WELL, PLEASE...

15:13.750 --> 15:17.250
BE PREPARED.

15:17.250 --> 15:18.333
HEY, UH...LOOK,

15:18.333 --> 15:22.542
"DESIGNED FOR THAT WOMAN'S
EXTRA PLEASURE."

15:22.542 --> 15:25.125
YEAH, HOW WOULD THEY KNOW?

15:25.125 --> 15:26.667
MAYBE THEY'RE DESIGNED
BY WOMEN.

15:26.667 --> 15:32.291
OH. GOOD POINT.

15:32.291 --> 15:34.083
SO, UH...
SHOULD WE GET SOME?

15:34.417 --> 15:36.583
WHAT?

15:36.583 --> 15:38.959
WELL, I MEAN YOU'RE RIGHT.
WE SHOULD BE PREPARED.

15:38.959 --> 15:42.583
IN CASE THAT MOOD STRIKES,
THEN, UH...

15:42.583 --> 15:44.625
WE'LL BE READY.

15:44.625 --> 15:46.750
ARE YOU BEING SERIOUS?

15:46.750 --> 15:49.417
IT'S NOT A BAD IDEA
TO HAVE THEM ON STAND-BY.

15:49.417 --> 15:51.917
I MEAN, WE CAN BE ADULTS
ABOUT THIS.

15:51.917 --> 15:52.667
UH...

15:52.667 --> 15:54.750
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

15:54.750 --> 15:56.250
ISN'T THERE ANYONE
ELSE I CAN READ WITH?

15:56.250 --> 15:57.708
Dawson: ABBY,
WE'RE SHORT ON TIME.

15:57.708 --> 15:59.625
IF YOU COULD JUST START
AT PAGE 3, THAT'D BE GREAT.

15:59.625 --> 16:01.834
SURE, DAWSON,
BUT CAN I JUST ASK
A QUICK QUESTION?

16:01.834 --> 16:02.625
WHAT IS IT, CHRIS?

16:02.625 --> 16:04.083
I JUST...

16:04.083 --> 16:06.959
I DON'T UNDERSTAND WHY
THEY DON'T EVER DO IT.

16:06.959 --> 16:09.542
I MEAN, YOU HAVE ALL
THE HOT FOREPLAY STUFF,

16:09.542 --> 16:10.959
BUT THEY NEVER HOOK UP.

16:10.959 --> 16:12.333
RIGHT.

16:12.333 --> 16:15.792
WELL, SEE, YOUR CHARACTER
BELIEVES THAT SOMETIMES
TRUE LOVE

16:15.792 --> 16:17.959
GOES BEYOND THAT WHICH
IS MERELY PHYSICAL.

16:17.959 --> 16:19.041
Chris: YEAH.

16:19.041 --> 16:20.792
YOU SEE, THAT'S JUST
THE PART I DON'T GET.

16:20.792 --> 16:23.458
YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT,
DAWSON, I THINK YOU
SHOULD RETHINK THAT PART.

16:23.458 --> 16:24.625
IT'S A LITTLE HEADY.

16:24.625 --> 16:25.834
OK, UH, YOU KNOW,
YOU GUYS,

16:25.834 --> 16:28.875
WHY DON'T WE JUST
KEEP MOVING WITH
THE SCENE, OK?

16:32.583 --> 16:35.834
I'VE WANTED TO...

16:35.834 --> 16:37.333
SO MANY TIMES.

16:37.333 --> 16:39.291
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW LONG
I'VE WRESTLED INTERNALLY

16:39.291 --> 16:42.333
WITH THE PSYCHOLOGICAL
REPERCUSSIONS
OF MY FEELINGS.

16:42.333 --> 16:45.208
Abby: I NEED SOME TIME
TO PROCESS HERE.

16:45.208 --> 16:47.250
MY ELECTRICAL SYNAPSES
ARE ON OVERLOAD.

16:47.250 --> 16:50.208
MY BRAIN SAYS ONE THING,
BUT MY HEART
SAYS SOMETHING ELSE.

16:50.208 --> 16:52.083
THAT I SHOULD CONSIDER
THE UNEQUIVOCAL,

16:52.083 --> 16:54.583
POSSIBLY DAMAGING,
HIGHLY IRRATIONAL,

16:54.583 --> 16:56.667
HYPNOTICALLY SCARRING,
PROPOSITION OF...

16:56.667 --> 16:58.625
OF LOVING YOU BACK.

16:58.625 --> 16:59.834
WAIT.

17:00.500 --> 17:02.625
UNH...

17:02.625 --> 17:04.791
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT,
YOU LUG-NECKED FREAK?

17:04.791 --> 17:06.208
A KISS.

17:06.208 --> 17:07.290
IT'S IN THE SCRIPT.

17:07.290 --> 17:09.125
THAT WAS YOUR TONGUE
IN MY MOUTH.

17:09.125 --> 17:12.165
SORRY, I WAS JUST
GETTING INTO THE ROLE.

17:12.165 --> 17:14.333
NO, YOU WERE TRYING
TO GET INTO MY PANTS.

17:14.333 --> 17:15.916
GOD, I'M GOING TO BE SICK.

17:19.791 --> 17:22.250
SHALL I CONTINUE?

17:22.250 --> 17:25.916
THAT'LL BE ALL.
THANK YOU.

17:25.916 --> 17:27.666
I'VE PUT LOTS OF FANTASY
THOUGHT INTO THIS,

17:27.666 --> 17:30.875
AND I WANT MY FIRST TIME
TO BE SPECIAL.

17:30.875 --> 17:32.208
YOU KNOW,
THE PERFECT EVENING.

17:32.208 --> 17:35.125
LIKE, DINNER AT A FRENCH
RESTAURANT,

17:35.125 --> 17:39.041
A ROMANTIC AFTER-DINNER
STROLL BY THE DOCK,

17:39.041 --> 17:41.875
AND THEN ONTO A NICE
HISTORIC BED AND BREAKFAST.

17:41.875 --> 17:44.083
A BED AND BREAKFAST?

17:44.083 --> 17:46.375
IT'S MY FANTASY,
GO WITH IT.

17:46.375 --> 17:48.625
LAVENDER CANDLES...AND, UH,

17:48.625 --> 17:52.125
SINATRA, OR SOMEBODY EQUALLY
AS OLD-STYLE AND ROMANTIC.

17:52.125 --> 17:55.375
OK. SCHEDULE
IN BATHROOM BREAKS,

17:55.375 --> 17:57.375
OR DOES THE POOR GUY
HAVE TO HOLD IT
ALL EVENING?

17:57.375 --> 18:00.875
OK, I'M SORRY, BUT DECIDING
TO LOSE MY VIRGINITY

18:00.875 --> 18:03.125
IS A HUGE DEAL, OK?

18:03.125 --> 18:06.333
I MEAN, I DIDN'T HOLD
ONTO IT FOR 16 YEARS

18:06.333 --> 18:08.625
JUST TO LOSE IT IN ONE
DRUNK FLEETING MOMENT

18:08.625 --> 18:11.667
IN SOME SKANKY BACK SEAT
OF A LATE MODEL AMERICAN
CAR, OK?

18:11.667 --> 18:13.417
DAMN!

18:13.417 --> 18:16.208
SOMEBODY'S
LEAKING ALL MY BEST
LOVEMAKING SECRETS.

18:18.041 --> 18:20.250
IT'S JUST THAT...

18:20.250 --> 18:23.375
I'M GOING TO REMEMBER THIS
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE,

18:23.375 --> 18:26.208
AND I JUST THINK THAT
IF WE PUT A LITTLE PLANNING
INTO IT,

18:26.208 --> 18:28.041
TO ENSURE THAT
IT'S WORTH REMEMBERING,

18:28.041 --> 18:29.333
IT WOULD BE REALLY NICE.

18:29.333 --> 18:34.000
I KNOW HOW IMPORTANT
THE FIRST TIME IS.

18:34.000 --> 18:36.708
BELIEVE ME,
OF ALL PEOPLE, I KNOW.

18:36.708 --> 18:38.291
AND I KNOW
WITH MY TAINTED PAST,

18:38.291 --> 18:42.000
I MIGHT NOT BE THE MOST
LIKELY OF CANDIDATES,

18:42.000 --> 18:45.208
BUT IF AND WHEN
YOU DO DECIDE IT'S
THE RIGHT TIME FOR YOU,

18:45.208 --> 18:47.125
I'D REALLY
LIKE TO BE THE ONE

18:47.125 --> 18:49.125
THAT HELPS TO MAKE IT
A MEMORABLE EVENING.

18:51.792 --> 18:54.792
WELL, WHEN YOU
TALK LIKE THAT,

18:54.792 --> 18:57.291
IT MAKES ME
WANT TO JUMP YOU.

18:57.291 --> 18:58.708
OH, REALLY?

18:58.708 --> 18:59.792
YES.

18:59.792 --> 19:02.375
[♪♪♪]

19:16.959 --> 19:18.834
Dawson:
IT'S JUST SO FRUSTRATING

19:18.834 --> 19:20.500
TO HAVE THIS DREAM
OF MAKING THIS MOVIE,

19:20.500 --> 19:21.667
TO ACTUALLY GET THE MONEY
TO MAKE THE MOVIE,

19:21.667 --> 19:25.875
AND THEN REALIZING THAT
IT STILL MIGHT NOT HAPPEN.

19:25.875 --> 19:27.834
JUST LIKE IN THE SCRIPT.

19:27.834 --> 19:30.792
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

19:30.792 --> 19:32.333
I MEAN, YOU AND JOEY.

19:32.333 --> 19:36.417
YOU'RE IN LOVE WITH HER
FOR 15 YEARS,

19:36.417 --> 19:39.333
AND THEN WHEN YOU'RE
JUST ABOUT TO HAVE HER,

19:39.333 --> 19:41.792
YOU LOSE HER. TRAGIC.

19:41.792 --> 19:45.375
THE SCRIPT
IS NOT ABOUT JOEY.

19:45.375 --> 19:48.166
DAWSON, GIVE ME A BREAK.
IT READS LIKE
AN AUTOBIOGRAPHY.

19:48.166 --> 19:51.500
IT'S FUNNY.
I THOUGHT THAT...

19:51.500 --> 19:53.291
WE HAD SOMETHING, TOO,
BUT...

19:53.291 --> 19:55.625
EVEN WITH MY FLAIR
FOR THE DRAMATIC,

19:55.625 --> 19:57.458
MY ROLE'S BEEN REDUCED
TO THE FIRST ACT.

19:57.458 --> 20:02.500
JEN, YOU WERE IMPORTANT
TO ME. YOU KNOW THAT.

20:02.500 --> 20:05.333
WAS I?

20:05.333 --> 20:08.000
ABSOLUTELY.

20:08.000 --> 20:11.041
MORE THAN YOU KNOW.

20:11.041 --> 20:15.417
THEN I--I WANT TO ASK
YOU SOMETHING, DAWSON--

20:15.417 --> 20:18.208
SINCE WE'RE FRIENDS
AND ALL--UM...

20:21.083 --> 20:22.834
WHAT DID YOU LIKE
ABOUT ME?

20:23.959 --> 20:25.166
WHAT DID I LIKE ABOUT YOU?

20:25.166 --> 20:29.041
WE HAVE FUN TOGETHER...
YOU KNOW...

20:29.041 --> 20:32.417
I MEAN, YOU...YOU OPEN
ME UP TO STUFF.

20:32.417 --> 20:34.583
SKINNY-DIPPING DIDN'T SUCK.

20:34.583 --> 20:37.542
YOU KNOW, YOU WERE...

20:37.542 --> 20:39.083
YOU WERE SEXY.

20:40.542 --> 20:41.542
WERE?

20:41.542 --> 20:44.125
ARE. ARE.

20:47.542 --> 20:50.542
YOU KNOW, I THINK THAT
CHRIS AND ABBY ARE RIGHT
ABOUT YOUR SCRIPT.

20:50.542 --> 20:55.792
I THINK THAT THE 2 YOUNG
LOVERS SHOULD DO IT.

20:55.792 --> 20:58.041
IT'S ABOUT ROMANCE,
NOT SEX.

20:58.041 --> 21:02.041
WHO SAYS THAT SEX CAN'T BE
ROMANTIC, DAWSON? COME ON.

21:02.041 --> 21:03.417
I MEAN, LOOK AT
YOUR TARGET AUDIENCE.

21:03.417 --> 21:06.458
I WANTED TO MAKE THE
LESS OBVIOUS CHOICE.

21:06.458 --> 21:07.458
[LAUGHS]

21:07.458 --> 21:09.166
THAT'S FUNNY WHEN YOU
THINK ABOUT IT.

21:09.166 --> 21:10.959
WHAT?

21:10.959 --> 21:15.917
JUST THAT, IF YOU HADN'T
GONE FOR SUCH AN OBVIOUS
CHOICE OF GIRL,

21:15.917 --> 21:19.208
MAYBE THE ENDING TO YOUR SCRIPT
WOULD HAVE BEEN A LITTLE
LESS OBVIOUS.

21:19.208 --> 21:22.125
[♪♪♪]

21:42.291 --> 21:43.625
Jack: I'M COMING OUT.

21:48.500 --> 21:49.875
UM...

21:51.375 --> 21:53.792
JACK McPHEE
REPORTING FOR DUTY.

21:53.792 --> 21:55.792
WHERE--WHERE DO YOU
WANT ME?

21:55.792 --> 21:58.583
UM, YOU COULD, UH,
SIT ON THE COUCH
OR--OR THE CHAIR.

21:58.583 --> 22:00.500
OR YOU COULD STAND,
OR I COULD MOVE.

22:00.500 --> 22:04.000
UH, WHY DON'T I JUST
TAKE THE COUCH?

22:04.000 --> 22:05.166
OK.

22:05.166 --> 22:07.834
YOU KNOW, JOEY, IF--IF
YOU'RE UNCOMFORTABLE AT ALL,

22:07.834 --> 22:09.792
I--I CAN, YOU KNOW, KEEP
THE TOWEL ON FOR A WHILE,

22:09.792 --> 22:11.500
JUST UNTIL
WE GET LOOSENED UP.

22:11.500 --> 22:14.125
YOU KNOW, YOU CAN KIND
OF SKETCH AROUND...

22:14.125 --> 22:15.333
IT.

22:15.333 --> 22:19.667
JACK, I'M FINE.
YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.

22:19.667 --> 22:22.625
UH--UH, OK.

22:26.667 --> 22:29.333
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE PROBABLY RIGHT.

22:29.333 --> 22:31.083
MAYBE--MAYBE THE TOWEL
IS A GOOD IDEA.

22:31.083 --> 22:33.375
I MEAN, IT'LL GIVE ME
A CHANCE TO CONCENTRATE
ON THE...

22:33.375 --> 22:35.333
THE TOP PART.

22:44.500 --> 22:45.875
OH, DEJA VU.

22:45.875 --> 22:48.667
THIS IS JUST LIKE
THAT SCENE FROM TITANIC.

22:48.667 --> 22:49.625
[JACK LAUGHS]

22:49.625 --> 22:50.917
OH, RIGHT. YEAH.

22:50.917 --> 22:53.291
EXCEPT I'M JACK AND...

22:53.291 --> 22:54.708
YOU'RE ROSE.

22:56.333 --> 22:58.834
ROLE REVERSAL.

22:58.834 --> 22:59.500
I LIKE IT.

23:05.792 --> 23:08.291
LOOK, JOEY, IF YOU'RE NOT
GONNA MAKE IT, WE CAN STOP
THIS AT ANY TIME.

23:08.291 --> 23:10.041
YOU KNOW, UM...

23:10.041 --> 23:11.708
MAYBE IF WE JUST
DIDN'T TALK.

23:11.708 --> 23:14.667
UM, THE MODEL IN CLASS
KINDA JUST SAT AND
STARED OUT THE WINDOW.

23:14.667 --> 23:16.708
AND, YOU KNOW,
SINCE WE ARE JUST...

23:16.708 --> 23:18.667
STARTING TO GET TO KNOW
EACH OTHER, I JUST...

23:18.667 --> 23:21.959
I'LL ADMIT IT HAS
MADE ME SLIGHTLY
UNCOMFORTABLE.

23:21.959 --> 23:26.083
WELL...JUST IMAGINE HOW
COMFORTABLE WE'RE GONNA
BE AROUND EACH OTHER

23:26.083 --> 23:28.375
AFTER TONIGHT.

23:32.333 --> 23:35.250
YOU KNOW, JACK, UM...
I CAN'T DO THIS.

23:35.250 --> 23:37.708
YOU KNOW,
I JUST DON'T THINK
THIS IS A GOOD IDEA.

23:37.708 --> 23:40.250
I MEAN, I TRIED TO BE
ADULT ABOUT THIS,

23:40.250 --> 23:41.750
AND NOT BEHAVE LIKE
LITTLE JOEY POTTER,

23:41.750 --> 23:44.708
BUT THE TRUTH IS, YOU KNOW,
I'M REALLY NOT THAT
EXPERIENCED WITH...

23:44.708 --> 23:46.917
UM, A LOT OF THINGS.

23:46.917 --> 23:49.583
AND I REALLY DON'T THINK
I COULD HANDLE SEEING YOU
NAKED RIGHT NOW,

23:49.583 --> 23:53.542
SO IF YOU COULD PROBABLY
JUST GET DRESSED
AND GO HOME, THAT WOULD...

23:53.542 --> 23:54.625
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR SKETCH?

23:54.625 --> 23:55.458
YEAH, I'LL FIGURE OUT
SOME WAY TO FUDGE IT.

23:55.458 --> 23:58.375
ARE YOU SURE?
YES, I'M SURE!

24:09.667 --> 24:10.708
WELL, UM...

24:10.708 --> 24:12.417
[CLEARS THROAT]

24:12.417 --> 24:14.959
MIGHT AS WELL
STAY NOW.

24:14.959 --> 24:18.458
UH...

24:22.750 --> 24:26.000
[♪♪♪]

24:38.959 --> 24:41.125
SO, UH, AHEM...
HOW'S IT LOOK?

24:41.125 --> 24:43.834
"IT"?

24:43.834 --> 24:46.000
OH, IT'S COMING ALONG FINE.
I'M SORRY.

24:46.000 --> 24:48.875
AND HOW YOU DOING?

24:48.875 --> 24:50.625
SURPRISINGLY WELL.

24:50.625 --> 24:54.500
YOU KNOW, NO SIGN
OF HEART FAILURE, SO...

24:55.542 --> 24:58.208
IT'S ACTUALLY--IT'S...
IT'S OK.

24:58.208 --> 25:01.708
IT FEELS KIND OF...

25:01.708 --> 25:03.041
NATURAL?

25:03.041 --> 25:05.625
UM...SORT OF.

25:05.625 --> 25:07.166
IT'S MORE LIKE
AN ACCOMPLISHMENT.

25:07.166 --> 25:10.083
I KNOW, THIS IS SOMETHING
THAT MOST PEOPLE WOULD
JUST ASSUME

25:10.083 --> 25:12.208
THAT JOEY COULD NOT DO.

25:12.208 --> 25:14.417
WHY IS THAT?

25:14.417 --> 25:17.000
I MEAN, YOU SEE HOW I LIVE.
I DON'T GET OUT MUCH, AND...

25:17.000 --> 25:20.625
I GUESS MY LIFE JUST SEEMS
KIND OF PLAIN SOMETIMES.

25:22.000 --> 25:23.041
DOES THAT BOTHER YOU?

25:23.041 --> 25:26.333
UM...YEAH, SOMETIMES.

25:28.000 --> 25:31.959
